{
  "id": "trane-xv80-pressure-switch",
  "brand": "Trane",
  "model": "XV80",
  "equipment_type": "furnace",
  "symptom": "Furnace inducer motor runs but burners never ignite. LED error code 33 (pressure switch stuck open). Inducer sounds normal. Flue and intake pipes appear clear from outside.",
  "diagnosis": "Pressure switch cannot close because of a blocked condensate drain trap. The XV80 is a 80% AFUE furnace but uses a condensate trap in the collector box \u2014 when clogged, negative pressure can't build in the vestibule, and the switch stays open. Less commonly: cracked pressure switch hose, or failed switch.",
  "part_number": "SWT02523 (Trane pressure switch) \u2014 but usually fixing the drain resolves it",
  "procedure": [
    "Kill power at the furnace switch.",
    "Locate the pressure switch \u2014 small round disc with a diaphragm, mounted near the inducer. Has a rubber hose running to the collector box.",
    "Inspect the hose for cracks, kinks, or moisture inside. Replace if damaged (1/4\" ID silicone hose).",
    "Remove the condensate drain hose from the collector box. Blow through it \u2014 if blocked, clear with compressed air or a pipe cleaner.",
    "Remove the collector box cover (if accessible) and clear any sludge or debris from the trap.",
    "Pour a small amount of water into the trap to re-prime it (traps must hold water to seal).",
    "With the hose reconnected, restore power. Let the inducer run and listen for the pressure switch to click closed (audible click within 15\u201330 seconds of inducer start).",
    "If the switch still won't close: jumper it briefly (for diagnosis ONLY, never leave jumped) to verify the rest of the ignition sequence works. If it fires, the switch or its port is the issue.",
    "Replace the pressure switch (SWT02523) if cleaning doesn't resolve. Verify the new switch closes within the inducer pre-purge period."
  ],
  "safety_notes": [
    "Never leave a pressure switch jumped \u2014 it exists to prevent combustion gas spillage into the living space.",
    "If the inducer motor sounds labored or different than normal, check for a cracked heat exchanger before proceeding.",
    "Condensate from a furnace can be mildly acidic \u2014 avoid skin contact and dispose properly."
  ],
  "estimated_minutes": 30,
  "tags": [
    "pressure switch",
    "error code 33",
    "stuck open",
    "drain trap",
    "XV80",
    "trane",
    "furnace",
    "inducer",
    "no ignition"
  ],
